l2tAdminState.name: l2tAdminState
l2tAdminState.description: This object defines the administrative state of the L2T protocol stack.

l2tAuthenticateIncomingTunnelSetupReques.name: l2tAuthenticateIncomingTunnelSetupRequests
l2tAuthenticateIncomingTunnelSetupReques.description: Defines whether the L2T protocol stack will REQUIRE the CHAP-like authentication mechanism to be present in all tunnel setup requests.

l2tTunnelDataFlowControl.name: l2tTunnelDataFlowControl
l2tTunnelDataFlowControl.description: This object determines whether or not L2T is to use flow control on the tunneled data packets.

l2tControlRecvPacketWindow.name: l2tControlRecvPacketWindow
l2tControlRecvPacketWindow.description: This object defines the Control Channel receive window size which is transmitted to the L2T peers.

l2tDataRecvPacketWindow.name: l2tDataRecvPacketWindow
l2tDataRecvPacketWindow.description: This object defines the Data Channel receive window size which is transmitted to the L2T peers.

l2tHelloTimer.name: l2tHelloTimer
l2tHelloTimer.description: This object defines the length of the inactivity timer in seconds which causes the L2T stack to transmit a keep-alive packet (known as a Hello packet).

l2tControlRetransmissions.name: l2tControlRetransmissions
l2tControlRetransmissions.description: This object defines the number of retransmissions which the L2T stack will attempt before assuming that the peer is no longer reachable. The default value for this object is zero (0) which results in the L2T stack not doing retransmissions.

l2tSecurityExtensions.name: l2tSecurityExtensions
l2tSecurityExtensions.description: This object defines whether the L2T protocol stack will require the L2T Security for all incoming tunnel setup requests.

l2tHistoryWindowSize.name: l2tHistoryWindowSize
l2tHistoryWindowSize.description: The window size of the L2T Tunnel History Table (l2tHistTunnelTable) and the L2T Session History Table (l2tHistSessTable). When retrieved by an SNMP GET or GET-NEXT request, this number specifies the maximum number of entries which will be maintained in each of these tables. When modified by an SNMP SET request, the device will set the value of this object as close as possible to the requested value based on implementation and available resources.

l2tAuthFailWindowSize.name: l2tAuthFailWindowSize
l2tAuthFailWindowSize.description: The window size of the L2T Tunnel Authentication Failure Table (l2tAuthFailTunnelTable) and the L2T User Authentication Failure Table (l2tAuthFailUserTable). When retrieved by an SNMP GET or GET-NEXT request, this number specifies the maximum number of entries which will be maintained in each of these tables. When modified by an SNMP SET request, the device will set the value of this object as close as possible to the requested value based on implementation and available resources.

l2tMibVersion.name: l2tMibVersion
l2tMibVersion.description: The level of the IBM L2T MIB.

l2tProtocolVersion.name: l2tProtocolVersion
l2tProtocolVersion.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the L2T protocol stack. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

l2tNumActiveTunnels.name: l2tNumActiveTunnels
l2tNumActiveTunnels.description: This object returns the number of L2T tunnels that are mandatory active.

l2tStatsNumActiveSessions.name: l2tStatsNumActiveSessions
l2tStatsNumActiveSessions.description: This object returns the number of L2T sessions that are mandatory active.

l2tTunnelStatsTable.name: l2tTunnelStatsTable
l2tTunnelStatsTable.description: The L2T tunnel status and statistics table.

l2tTunnelStatsEntry.name: l2tTunnelStatsEntry
l2tTunnelStatsEntry.description: An L2T tunnel interface stats entry.

l2tTunnelLocalTunnelControlId.name: l2tTunnelLocalTunnelControlId
l2tTunnelLocalTunnelControlId.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

l2tTunnelPeerTunnelControlId.name: l2tTunnelPeerTunnelControlId
l2tTunnelPeerTunnelControlId.description: This object contains the remote tunnel Identifier.

l2tTunnelControlState.name: l2tTunnelControlState
l2tTunnelControlState.description: This field contains the mandatory state of the control tunnel.

l2tTunnelLocalInitConnection.name: l2tTunnelLocalInitConnection
l2tTunnelLocalInitConnection.description: This object indicates whether the tunnel was generated locally or not. When this object returns a value of true(1) the tunnel was locally generated.

l2tTunnelLocalRecvPktWindow.name: l2tTunnelLocalRecvPktWindow
l2tTunnelLocalRecvPktWindow.description: This object contains the local receive window size.

l2tTunnelRemoteRecvPktWindow.name: l2tTunnelRemoteRecvPktWindow
l2tTunnelRemoteRecvPktWindow.description: This object contains the remote receive window size.

l2tTunnelCtlTunnelFlwCtlTimeouts.name: l2tTunnelCtlTunnelFlwCtlTimeouts
l2tTunnelCtlTunnelFlwCtlTimeouts.description: This object contains the number of timeouts due to flow control.

l2tTunnelRemoteHostName.name: l2tTunnelRemoteHostName
l2tTunnelRemoteHostName.description: This object contains the host name of the L2T peer.

l2tTunnelNextSendSeq.name: l2tTunnelNextSendSeq
l2tTunnelNextSendSeq.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for the control channel.

l2tTunnelNextRecvSeq.name: l2tTunnelNextRecvSeq
l2tTunnelNextRecvSeq.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number for the control channel.

l2tTunnelRemoteVendorName.name: l2tTunnelRemoteVendorName
l2tTunnelRemoteVendorName.description: This object identifies the vendor name of the peer's L2T implementation.

l2tTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision.name: l2tTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision
l2tTunnelRemoteFirmwareRevision.description: This object contains the L2T peer's firmware revision number.

l2tTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion.name: l2tTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion
l2tTunnelRemoteProtocolVersion.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the L2T protocol stack. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

l2tTunnelActiveSessions.name: l2tTunnelActiveSessions
l2tTunnelActiveSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions in use for this tunnel.

l2tTunnelPrevSessions.name: l2tTunnelPrevSessions
l2tTunnelPrevSessions.description: The total number of previously actively sessions which used this tunnel.

l2tTunnelUpTime.name: l2tTunnelUpTime
l2tTunnelUpTime.description: The length of time the tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

l2tTunnelType.name: l2tTunnelType
l2tTunnelType.description: The type of Layer-2 Tunnel. Possible values are: 1 = Layer-2 Tunnel Protocol Tunnel, 2 = Layer-2 Forwarding Tunnel, 3 = Point-to-Point Tunnel Protocol Tunnel.

l2tTunnelInOctets.name: l2tTunnelInOctets
l2tTunnelInOctets.description: The number of octets received by this tunnel.

l2tTunnelInPkts.name: l2tTunnelInPkts
l2tTunnelInPkts.description: The number of packets received by this tunnel.

l2tTunnelInDiscards.name: l2tTunnelInDiscards
l2tTunnelInDiscards.description: The number of packets which were discarded during receive processing.

l2tTunnelOutOctets.name: l2tTunnelOutOctets
l2tTunnelOutOctets.description: The number of octets sent by this tunnel.

l2tTunnelOutPkts.name: l2tTunnelOutPkts
l2tTunnelOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent by this tunnel.

l2tTunnelOutDiscards.name: l2tTunnelOutDiscards
l2tTunnelOutDiscards.description: The number of packets which were discarded during send processing.

l2tTunnelStatus.name: l2tTunnelStatus
l2tTunnelStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to bring the tunnel down by setting value of this object to destroy(2). This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row.

l2tSessionStatsTable.name: l2tSessionStatsTable
l2tSessionStatsTable.description: The L2T session status and statistics table.

l2tSessionStatsEntry.name: l2tSessionStatsEntry
l2tSessionStatsEntry.description: An L2T session interface stats entry.

l2tSessionLocalControlTunnelId.name: l2tSessionLocalControlTunnelId
l2tSessionLocalControlTunnelId.description: This object contains the control Channel Tunnel identifier for this session.

l2tSessionLocalCallId.name: l2tSessionLocalCallId
l2tSessionLocalCallId.description: This object contains the local call identifier for the session.

l2tSessionRemoteCallId.name: l2tSessionRemoteCallId
l2tSessionRemoteCallId.description: This object contains the remote call identifier for the session.

l2tSessionPeerName.name: l2tSessionPeerName
l2tSessionPeerName.description: This object identifies the peer session name on this interface. This is typically the login name of the remote user.

l2tSessionLineState.name: l2tSessionLineState
l2tSessionLineState.description: This object contains the current state of the session.

l2tSessionCallDeviceNumber.name: l2tSessionCallDeviceNumber
l2tSessionCallDeviceNumber.description: The internal interface number used for the session.

l2tSessionCallSerialNumber.name: l2tSessionCallSerialNumber
l2tSessionCallSerialNumber.description: This object contains the serial number that applies to the session.

l2tSessionConnectBps.name: l2tSessionConnectBps
l2tSessionConnectBps.description: This object returns the baud rate which this session was established at.

l2tSessionCallBearerType.name: l2tSessionCallBearerType
l2tSessionCallBearerType.description: This object returns the bearer type that applies to this session.

l2tSessionFramingType.name: l2tSessionFramingType
l2tSessionFramingType.description: This object returns the framing type used for this session.

l2tSessionLocalRecvPacketWindow.name: l2tSessionLocalRecvPacketWindow
l2tSessionLocalRecvPacketWindow.description: This object returns the local receive window size for this session.

l2tSessionRemoteRecvPacketWindow.name: l2tSessionRemoteRecvPacketWindow
l2tSessionRemoteRecvPacketWindow.description: This object returns the remote receive window size for this session.

l2tSessionDataRecvOctets.name: l2tSessionDataRecvOctets
l2tSessionDataRecvOctets.description: The number of octets received on the data tunnel for this session. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be uncompressed.

l2tSessionDataRecvDecompOctets.name: l2tSessionDataRecvDecompOctets
l2tSessionDataRecvDecompOctets.description: The number of uncompressed octets received on the data tunnel for this session. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is uncompressed. If compression is not in use, this value will match the value of l2tSessionDataRecvOctets.

l2tSessionDataRecvPackets.name: l2tSessionDataRecvPackets
l2tSessionDataRecvPackets.description: The number packets received on the data tunnel for this session.

l2tSessionDataRecvDiscards.name: l2tSessionDataRecvDiscards
l2tSessionDataRecvDiscards.description: The number packets which were discarded during the data tunnels receive processing for this session.

l2tSessionDataSendOctets.name: l2tSessionDataSendOctets
l2tSessionDataSendOctets.description: The number of octets sent on the data tunnel for this session. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet was compressed. If compression is not in use, this value will match the value of l2tSessionDataRecvUncompOctets.

l2tSessionDataSendUncompOctets.name: l2tSessionDataSendUncompOctets
l2tSessionDataSendUncompOctets.description: The number of uncompressed octets sent on the data tunnel for this session. This value is is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

l2tSessionDataSendPackets.name: l2tSessionDataSendPackets
l2tSessionDataSendPackets.description: The number packets sent on the data tunnel for this session.

l2tSessionDataSendDiscards.name: l2tSessionDataSendDiscards
l2tSessionDataSendDiscards.description: The number packets which were discarded during the data tunnels send processing for this session.

l2tSessionDataFlowControlTimeouts.name: l2tSessionDataFlowControlTimeouts
l2tSessionDataFlowControlTimeouts.description: This object returns the total number of flow control time-outs seen on the data Tunnel for this session.

l2tSessionNextSendSeq.name: l2tSessionNextSendSeq
l2tSessionNextSendSeq.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for for this session.

l2tSessionNextRecvSeq.name: l2tSessionNextRecvSeq
l2tSessionNextRecvSeq.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number for this session.

l2tSessionRemotePPD.name: l2tSessionRemotePPD
l2tSessionRemotePPD.description: This object contains the Packet Processing Delay for the session.

l2tSessionAuthMethod.name: l2tSessionAuthMethod
l2tSessionAuthMethod.description: This object contains the proxy authentication method employed by the LAC for the session.

l2tSessionEncryptDecrypt.name: l2tSessionEncryptDecrypt
l2tSessionEncryptDecrypt.description: This object reflects whether or not the encryption and and decryption is being performed for the session.

l2tSessionUpTime.name: l2tSessionUpTime
l2tSessionUpTime.description: The length of time the session has been active in hundredths of seconds.

l2tSessionStatus.name: l2tSessionStatus
l2tSessionStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to bring the session down by setting value of this object to destroy(2). This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row.

l2tUdpConfigEntry.name: l2tUdpConfigEntry
l2tUdpConfigEntry.description: An L2T session interface configuration entry.

l2tUdpPeerAddress.name: l2tUdpPeerAddress
l2tUdpPeerAddress.description: This object is used to configure the remote tunnel endpoints IP address.

l2tUdpPeerPort.name: l2tUdpPeerPort
l2tUdpPeerPort.description: This object is used to configure the remote tunnel endpoints UDP port.

l2tUdpStatsEntry.name: l2tUdpStatsEntry
l2tUdpStatsEntry.description: An L2T session interface configuration entry.

l2tUdpPeerIpAddress.name: l2tUdpPeerIpAddress
l2tUdpPeerIpAddress.description: The peer IP Address of the tunnel.

l2tUdpLocalIpAddress.name: l2tUdpLocalIpAddress
l2tUdpLocalIpAddress.description: The local IP Address of the tunnel.

l2tAuthTunnelSuccesses.name: l2tAuthTunnelSuccesses
l2tAuthTunnelSuccesses.description: The number of successful tunnel authentications performed.

l2tAuthTunnelFailures.name: l2tAuthTunnelFailures
l2tAuthTunnelFailures.description: The number of tunnel authentications which failed.

l2tAuthUserSuccesses.name: l2tAuthUserSuccesses
l2tAuthUserSuccesses.description: The number of successful user authentications performed.

l2tAuthUserFailures.name: l2tAuthUserFailures
l2tAuthUserFailures.description: The number of user authentications which failed.

l2tAuthFailTunnelTable.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelTable
l2tAuthFailTunnelTable.description: The L2T tunnel authentication failure table.

l2tAuthFailTunnelEntry.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelEntry
l2tAuthFailTunnelEntry.description: An L2T tunnel authentication failure entry.

l2tAuthFailTunnelIndex.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelIndex
l2tAuthFailTunnelIndex.description: The index of the tunnel authentication failure table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel authentication failure. It will wrap at 65535.

l2tAuthFailTunnelHostName.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelHostName
l2tAuthFailTunnelHostName.description: The host name used on the failed tunnel authentication attempt.

l2tAuthFailTunnelIpAddress.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelIpAddress
l2tAuthFailTunnelIpAddress.description: The IP address associated with the failed tunnel authentication attempt.

l2tAuthFailTunnelTime.name: l2tAuthFailTunnelTime
l2tAuthFailTunnelTime.description: The time of the failure in hundredths of seconds.

l2tAuthFailUserTable.name: l2tAuthFailUserTable
l2tAuthFailUserTable.description: The L2T user authentication failure table.

l2tAuthFailUserEntry.name: l2tAuthFailUserEntry
l2tAuthFailUserEntry.description: An L2T user authentication failure entry.

l2tAuthFailUserIndex.name: l2tAuthFailUserIndex
l2tAuthFailUserIndex.description: The index of the user authentication failure table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each user authentication failure. It will wrap at 65535.

l2tAuthFailUserId.name: l2tAuthFailUserId
l2tAuthFailUserId.description: The user name used on the failed authentication attempt.

l2tAuthFailUserTime.name: l2tAuthFailUserTime
l2tAuthFailUserTime.description: The time of the failure in hundredths of seconds.

l2tHistTunnelIndex.name: l2tHistTunnelIndex
l2tHistTunnelIndex.description: The index of the tunnel history table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 65535.

l2tHistTunnelTunnelIndex.name: l2tHistTunnelTunnelIndex
l2tHistTunnelTunnelIndex.description: The value which was used as the tunnel stats table index.

l2tHistTunnelRemoteHostName.name: l2tHistTunnelRemoteHostName
l2tHistTunnelRemoteHostName.description: The remote host name which was used for this previous tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelRemoteIpAddress.name: l2tHistTunnelRemoteIpAddress
l2tHistTunnelRemoteIpAddress.description: The remote IP address which was used for this previous tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelRemotePort.name: l2tHistTunnelRemotePort
l2tHistTunnelRemotePort.description: The remote UDP port which was used for this previous tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelLocalIpAddress.name: l2tHistTunnelLocalIpAddress
l2tHistTunnelLocalIpAddress.description: The local IP address which was used for this previous tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelLocalPort.name: l2tHistTunnelLocalPort
l2tHistTunnelLocalPort.description: The local UDP port which was used for this previous tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelUpTime.name: l2tHistTunnelUpTime
l2tHistTunnelUpTime.description: The length of time the tunnel was active in hundredths of seconds.

l2tHistTunnelTotalSessions.name: l2tHistTunnelTotalSessions
l2tHistTunnelTotalSessions.description: The total number of sessions which used this tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelType.name: l2tHistTunnelType
l2tHistTunnelType.description: The type of Layer-2 Tunnel. Possible values are 1 = Layer-2 Tunnel Protocol Tunnel, 2 = Layer-2 Forwarding Tunnel, 3 = Point-to-Point Tunnel Protocol Tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelInOctets.name: l2tHistTunnelInOctets
l2tHistTunnelInOctets.description: The number of octets received by this tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelInPkts.name: l2tHistTunnelInPkts
l2tHistTunnelInPkts.description: The number of packets received by this tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelInDiscards.name: l2tHistTunnelInDiscards
l2tHistTunnelInDiscards.description: The number of packets which were discarded during receive processing.

l2tHistTunnelOutOctets.name: l2tHistTunnelOutOctets
l2tHistTunnelOutOctets.description: The number of octets sent by this tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelOutPkts.name: l2tHistTunnelOutPkts
l2tHistTunnelOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent by this tunnel.

l2tHistTunnelOutDiscards.name: l2tHistTunnelOutDiscards
l2tHistTunnelOutDiscards.description: The number of packets which were discarded during send processing.

l2tHistSessIndex.name: l2tHistSessIndex
l2tHistSessIndex.description: The index of the session history table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 65535.

l2tHistSessTunnelIndex.name: l2tHistSessTunnelIndex
l2tHistSessTunnelIndex.description: The value which was used as the tunnel stats table index.

l2tHistSessLocalCallId.name: l2tHistSessLocalCallId
l2tHistSessLocalCallId.description: The value which was used as the session stats table index.

l2tHistSessRemoteIpAddress.name: l2tHistSessRemoteIpAddress
l2tHistSessRemoteIpAddress.description: The remote IP address which was used for this session.

l2tHistSessLocalIpAddress.name: l2tHistSessLocalIpAddress
l2tHistSessLocalIpAddress.description: The local IP address which was used for this session.

l2tHistSessUpTime.name: l2tHistSessUpTime
l2tHistSessUpTime.description: The length of time the session was been active in hundredths of seconds.

l2tHistSessDataRecvOctets.name: l2tHistSessDataRecvOctets
l2tHistSessDataRecvOctets.description: The number of octets received on the data tunnel for this session. This value was accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be uncompressed.

l2tHistSessDataRecvPackets.name: l2tHistSessDataRecvPackets
l2tHistSessDataRecvPackets.description: The number packets received on the data tunnel for this session.

l2tHistSessDataRecvDiscards.name: l2tHistSessDataRecvDiscards
l2tHistSessDataRecvDiscards.description: The number packets which were discarded during the data tunnels receive processing for this session.

l2tHistSessDataSendOctets.name: l2tHistSessDataSendOctets
l2tHistSessDataSendOctets.description: The number of octets sent on the data tunnel for this session. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet was compressed.

l2tHistSessDataSendPackets.name: l2tHistSessDataSendPackets
l2tHistSessDataSendPackets.description: The number packets sent on the data tunnel for this session.

l2tHistSessDataSendDiscards.name: l2tHistSessDataSendDiscards
l2tHistSessDataSendDiscards.description: The number packets which were discarded during the data tunnels send processing for this session.

l2tHistSessAuthMethod.name: l2tHistSessAuthMethod
l2tHistSessAuthMethod.description: This object contains the proxy authentication method which was employed by the LAC for the session.

l2tHistSessEncryptDecrypt.name: l2tHistSessEncryptDecrypt
l2tHistSessEncryptDecrypt.description: This object reflects whether or not the encryption and and decryption is being performed for the session.

l2tHostIndex.name: l2tHostIndex
l2tHostIndex.description: The index of the host table.

l2tHostName.name: l2tHostName
l2tHostName.description: The host name which may used for a Layer-2 tunnel.

l2tHostIpAddress.name: l2tHostIpAddress
l2tHostIpAddress.description: The IP Address associated with the host name.

l2tHostTunnelStatus.name: l2tHostTunnelStatus
l2tHostTunnelStatus.description: The current tunnel status of the host.

l2tTunnelConnectTestTable.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestTable
l2tTunnelConnectTestTable.description: The L2T tunnel connectivity test table.

l2tTunnelConnectTestEntry.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestEntry
l2tTunnelConnectTestEntry.description: An L2T tunnel connectivity test entry.

l2tTunnelConnectTestIndex.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestIndex
l2tTunnelConnectTestIndex.description: The index of the tunnel connectivity test table. The value of the index is a number which was used during row creation.

l2tTunnelConnectTestHostName.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestHostName
l2tTunnelConnectTestHostName.description: The host name used to establish a Layer-2 tunnel. This object is used to trigger a connectivity test to a specific host. A new test is triggered by SETTING this object using a non-existent index and SETTING l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus to createAndGo. For example to trigger a new connectivity test when the table currently contains row 1 through 4, one would send a SET as follows: SNMP SET l2tTunnelConnectHostName.5 = Host-To-Test l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus.5 = createAndGo See l2tHostName for the possible host names which may be specified. Existing entries may NOT be modified.

l2tTunnelConnectTestResult.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestResult
l2tTunnelConnectTestResult.description: The result of the tunnel connectivity test. 1 = test is in progress 2 = test ended successfully 3 = tunnel is already active 4 = host did not respond 5 = local authentication failure 6 = remote authentication failure.

l2tTunnelConnectTestType.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestType
l2tTunnelConnectTestType.description: The type of Layer-2 Tunnel. Possible values are: 1 = Layer-2 Tunnel Protocol Tunnel 2 = Layer-2 Forwarding Tunnel 3 = Point-to-Point Tunnel Protocol Tunnel 99 = no tunnel created.

l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus.name: l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus
l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus.description: The status of the test entry. Possible values are: 1 = active entry 4 = createAndGo This object is used to trigger a connectivity test to a specific host. A new test is triggered by SETTING this object to createAndGo using a non-existent index and SETTING l2tTunnelConnectTestHostName to a specific host name. For example to trigger a new connectivity test when the table currently contains row 1 through 4, one would send a SET as follows: SNMP SET l2tTunnelConnectHostName.5 = Host-To-Test l2tTunnelConnectTestStatus.5 = createAndGo See l2tHostName for the possible host names which may be specified. Existing entries may NOT be modified.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestTable.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestTable
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestTable.description: The L2T tunnel response time test table.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestEntry.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestEntry
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestEntry.description: An L2T tunnel response time test entry.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestIndex.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestIndex
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestIndex.description: The index of the tunnel connectivity test table. The value of the index is a number which was used during row creation.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestHostName.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestHostName
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestHostName.description: The host name used to test the round-trip response time of an existing Layer-2 Tunnel. This object is used to trigger a response time test of an existing Layer-2 to a specific host. A new test is triggered by SETTING this object using a non-existent index and SETTING l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus to createAndGo. For example to trigger a new connectivity test when the table currently contains row 1 through 4, one would send a SET as follows: SNMP SET l2tTunnelRspTimeHostName.5 = Host-To-Test l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus.5 = createAndGo See l2tHistTunnelRemoteHostName for the possible host names which may be specified. Existing entries may NOT be modified.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestResult.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestResult
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestResult.description: The result of the tunnel connectivity test. 1 = test is in progress 2 = test ended successfully 3 = host did not respond 4 = a tunnel to this host is NOT available.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestRtripTime.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestRtripTime
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestRtripTime.description: The round time in milliseconds of response time test.

l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus.name: l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus
l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus.description: The status of the test entry. Possible values are: 1 = active entry 4 = createAndGo This object is used to trigger a response time test of an existing Layer-2 to a specific host. A new test is triggered by SETTING this object using a non-existent index to createAndGo and SETTING l2tTunnelRspTimeHostName to a specific host. For example to trigger a new response time test when the table currently contains row 1 through 4, one would send a SET as follows: SNMP SET l2tTunnelRspTimeHostName.5 = Host-To-Test l2tTunnelRspTimeTestStatus.5 = createAndGo See l2tHistTunnelRemoteHostName for the possible host names which may be specified. Existing entries may NOT be modified.

l2tTrapCntlTunnelStart.name: l2tTrapCntlTunnelStart
l2tTrapCntlTunnelStart.description: This object defines the administrative state of sending the L2T Tunnel Start TRAP

l2tTrapCntlTunnelStop.name: l2tTrapCntlTunnelStop
l2tTrapCntlTunnelStop.description: This object defines the administrative state of sending the L2T Tunnel Stop TRAP

l2tTrapCntlAuthFailTunnel.name: l2tTrapCntlAuthFailTunnel
l2tTrapCntlAuthFailTunnel.description: This object defines the administrative state of sending the L2T Tunnel Authentication Failure TRAP

l2tTrapCntlAuthFailUser.name: l2tTrapCntlAuthFailUser
